What's included

TT-UI Library is downloadable in two forms, within which you'll find the following directories and files, logically grouping common resources and providing both compiled and minified variations.

Precompiled TT-UI Library

Once downloaded, unzip the compressed folder to see the structure of (the compiled) Bootstrap. You'll see something like this:

{% highlight bash %} tecnotree-ui-library/ ├── css/ │ ├── tecnotree-ui-library.css │ └── tecnotree-ui-library.css.map └── sass/ ├── components/ │ ├── _buttons.scss │ ├── _forms.scss │ ├── _glyphicons.scss │ ├── _layout.scss │ ├── _modals.scss │ ├── _multiselect-dropdown.scss │ ├── _navbar.scss │ ├── _navs.scss │ ├── _panels.scss │ ├── _spinner.scss │ ├── _statusbar.scss │ ├── _suggestion-box.scss │ └── _table.scss │ └── _wizard.scss ├── tecnotree-ui-library.scss ├── tecnotree-ui-library-custom-variables.scss └── tecnotree-ui-library-components.scss {% endhighlight %}

Source code

The Source code download includes the precompiled CSS, JavaScript, and font assets, along with source Sass, JavaScript, and documentation. More specifically, it includes the following and more:

{% highlight bash %} tecnotree-ui-library/ ├── dist/ │ ├── css/ │ └── sass/ ├── src/ │ ├── scripts/ │ ├── css/ │ └── sass/ ├── examples/ └── docs/ {% endhighlight %}

The src/ folder is the source code for our SASS, CSS and JS. The dist/ folder includes everything listed in the precompiled download section above. The docs/ folder includes the source code for our documentation, and examples/ of usage. Beyond that, any other included file provides support for packages, license information, and development.
